 march frederick g leonard sold his interests in both stores to maria and odo stade and robert and emma holmes the latter the two silent_partners that year the store had to be enlarged once more and presently a rare_book_section was added by this time the hollywood bookstore had become known from coast to coast those were busy years for maria and odo the sales in both departments reached the half million mark by when in the booksellers convention was held in los angeles odo was chosen bookseller of the pacific coast
